spanishExample: Tienes que callarte o los dos terminarán peleando.
englishTranslation: You have to shut up or you two will end up fighting.

spanishExample: ¡No pelees! ¡Puede ser malo para tu cabello!
englishTranslation: Don’t fight! It might be bad for your hair!

spanishExample: Temen que quieran pelear.
englishTranslation: They fear they want to fight.

spanishExample: El médico me dijo que tengo buena salud.
englishTranslation: The medic told me I have good health.

spanishExample: Eso es lo que ella temía, porque si peleamos puede ser malo para sus oídos.
englishTranslation: That’s what she feared, because if we fight it might be bad for her ears.

spanishExample: Él teme que yo no sea feliz, pero lo soy.
englishTranslation: He fears that I’m not happy, but I am.

spanishExample: ¡Cállese y escuche al enfermero!
englishTranslation: (Formal) Shut up and listen to the nurse(m)!

spanishExample: Esta enfermedad le hizo algo a su voz.
englishTranslation: This disease did something to her voice.

spanishExample: Se teme que la gente pelee.
englishTranslation: It is feared that people fight.

spanishExample: Se han callado y nadie sabe que él estaba enfermo.
englishTranslation: They have shut up and nobody knows that he was sick.

spanishExample: Ella no quiere que yo pelee porque he peleado mucho.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want me to fight because I’ve fought a lot.

spanishExample: Ella temía que la fiesta no fuera aquí.
englishTranslation: She feared the party wasn’t here.

spanishExample: Cuando pelees, ella se tendrá que callar.
englishTranslation: When you fight, she will have to shut up.

spanishExample: No creo que ella lo tema, porque no peleas mucho.
englishTranslation: I don’t think she fears it, because you don’t fight much.

spanishExample: Me temo que la boda no es aquí.
englishTranslation: I’m afraid the wedding isn’t here.

spanishExample: No quiere que tema por mi brazo.
englishTranslation: He doesn’t want me to fear for my arm.

spanishExample: Yo no peleo, pero pelearé si ellos pelean.
englishTranslation: I don’t fight, but I will fight if they fight.

spanishExample: La comida estaba buena, pero faltaban otras cosas.
englishTranslation: The food was good, but other things were missing.

spanishExample: Nos tememos que ella no pelea.
englishTranslation: We’re afraid she doesn’t fight.

spanishExample: Quiero que ellos peleen y ellos quieren que yo me calle.
englishTranslation: I want them to fight and they want me to shut up.

spanishExample: Nunca peleamos, ¡así que callénse!
englishTranslation: We never fight, so shut up(plural)!

spanishExample: Temes por tu alma.
englishTranslation: You fear for your soul.

spanishExample: Quiero que te calles, no hay nada que temer.
englishTranslation: I want you to shut up, there isn’t anything to fear.

spanishExample: ¡Peleen para que yo me calle!
englishTranslation: (Plural) Fight so that I shut up!

spanishExample: ¡Ten cuidado con la oreja!
englishTranslation: Be careful with your ear!
